{
  "stem": "7744.2",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I don't know if he looked for my brother or not, because I-- I don't really know if he thought that he was alive or not, but he looked for my mother and myself.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And he found me in Sweden.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I imagine that in those days, everybody was finding-- making every effort to find, because there was the Swedish Red Cross, and the World Red Cross, and the [INAUDIBLE], and people were looking for people.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So he found me.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And he, at that time, was still in Germany.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] He was sick as well, but-- and I don't know which camps he was in, but he survived the war.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And then, through the family, I also had some other family in New York, by the name of Biller.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "They were somewhat further removed.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Cousins of second, third-removed cousins.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And somehow they found out that I was there, maybe through my aunt here.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And I started receiving parcels into Sweden with condensed milk and chocolate.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And-- and-- and in fact, one of the cousins was a part-owner in the Hershey chocolates.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "So I had a lot of chocolates sent to me, and all this.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "So that's in-- in Sweden.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And in Sweden, what was very interesting too, that we really and truly had a learning situation where the [NON-ENGLISH] from Israel and some of the people, some of the Jewish people, and-- and others, they made sure that we were being taught.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "It's in Sweden that I learned to read.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "It's in Sweden that I learned to write.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "It's in Sweden that I spoke Hebrew extremely well and learned the grammar and learned songs.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And I think that the effort was to prepare us as halutzim to go to Israel.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
